// Adversarial: CircuitBreaker chip accumulates a counter on every perfect bump, cycling
// through power states when the counter threshold is reached. AlwaysPerfect input
// guarantees a perfect bump on every breaker contact, so the CircuitBreaker counter
// advances at the maximum possible rate. Dense layout ensures the bolt reaches the breaker
// frequently, driving counter cycles as fast as the physics frame rate allows. The adversarial
// risk: if the CircuitBreaker state machine has a fencepost error in its cycle threshold, or
// if the power-state-change handler fires twice in a single frame during counter rollover,
// NoEntityLeaks fires for orphaned effect entities or BoltSpeedAccurate catches stat
// divergence from double-applied multipliers. NoNaN guards against overflow in counter or
// speed accumulator arithmetic. max_bolt_count raised to 16 to accommodate any bolt-spawn
// effects that CircuitBreaker's power states may trigger.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(AlwaysPerfect),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltCountReasonable, BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    invariant_params: (max_bolt_count: 16),
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 3137,
    chip_selections: ["Circuit Breaker"],
)
